text_context: wacac is pleased to host college fairs in california and nevada for high school students, their parents, and high school counselors. all of wacac’s fairs are free to attend and include free parking. we typically welcome representatives from more than 100 institutions at our events!
label: Other

text_context: prior to attending a wacac college fair, students and parents can register using a special link to receive an event barcode.
label: Other

text_context: after registering, you’ll get a reminder with your personal barcode two hours before the fair.
label: Other

text_context: at the fair, show your barcode to colleges. they’ll scan it to get your information.
label: Other

text_context: , you’ll get a report with information about all of the colleges that scanned your barcode. you’ll also start receiving information directly from the colleges about the application process, financial aid, and important deadlines.
label: Other

text_context: wacac college fair exhibitors play a major role in the success of each of our programs. the of the western association for college admission counseling, along with members of the local planning committee are responsible for creating a professional and safe environment for the delivery of wacac’s college fair program.
label: Other

text_context: wacac college fair exhibitor rules and regulations:
label: Other

text_context: our college fairs are for two- and four-year colleges and universities that are regionally accredited. on a space-available basis, we may accommodate some non-profit organizational members who assist students with the transition from high school to college. wacac reserves the right to refuse the registration of any institution or organization. independent counselors and/or educational consultants are not eligible. non-profits who would like to exhibit, should reach out to the college fair chair before registering to see if accommodations can be made.
label: Other

text_context: representatives must present clear and accurate information concerning their institution or agency while avoiding ambiguous, questionable, or false information about competing institutions and agencies.
label: Other

text_context: only full-time admissions officers, institutional representatives, delegated salaried school officials, or trained alumni shall represent schools or agencies during wacac programs. use of current students or recruits during wacac fairs will not be allowed.
label: Other

text_context: representatives are expected to be on time and stay until the program has been completed.
label: Other

text_context: representatives are expected to follow the cancellation policy. in the event of an emergency, the representative scheduled for the event has the responsibility of contacting the host coordinator as soon as the representative knows he or she will be unable to attend. registration fees are non-transferable.
label: Other

text_context: promotional giveaways (including raffles and drawings) and gimmick items (including, but not limited to, shopping bags, t-shirts, buttons, key chains, stickers, posters, decals, etc.) are strictly prohibited. appropriate items to distribute to students include brochures, catalogs, pens, pencils, and other literature pertaining to the institution.
label: Other

text_context: one piece of visual equipment will be permitted per table as long the power source is self-contained. wacac and/or the host site will not provide electricity, batteries, extension cords, etc. the audio-visual equipment should not interfere with other exhibitors.
label: Other

text_context: representatives may represent only one institution or agency and must agree not to recruit students for another institution.
label: Other

text_context: recruitment is restricted to behind the parameters of the table.
label: Other

text_context: tables are restricted to two representatives per table.
label: Other

text_context: representatives are required to dress in business or business casual (no t-shirts or blue jeans) for all programs.
label: Other

text_context: in order to minimize problems of congestion and blocked visibility, displays cannot exceed or obstruct the view of adjacent tables and should be no larger than 6ft high x 3ft wide. tablecloths or drops are permitted.
label: Other

text_context: failure to adhere to these guidelines will result in your institution being asked to vacate your table at the wacac fair.
label: Other
